We should continue matching the Android keycodes, which would have us adding:

``` java
public static final int NUMPAD_DIVIDE = 154;
public static final int NUMPAD_MULTIPLY = 155;
public static final int NUMPAD_SUBTRACT= 156;
public static final int NUMPAD_ADD = 157;
public static final int NUMPAD_DOT = 158;
public static final int NUMPAD_COMMA= 159;
public static final int NUMPAD_ENTER = 160;
```

And potentially more, if we want additional defined keycodes from Android.

@MobiDevelop Agreed, that seems like a very good idea. Edited my post with corresponding vars... good to know they're based on values from https://android.googlesource.com/platform/frameworks/native/+/master/include/input/KeycodeLabels.h - IMO it's worthwhile to document that in Input.java if that's out desired pattern.

NB this is the mapping code I use in my fork; if You deem it sensible, I'll submit it to trunk.
